{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T12:02:27.023Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Self-Attention — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Self-Attention Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Self-attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is an attention mechanism where "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "every token in a sequence attends to every other token in the same sequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — including itself — to compute contextual representations. The word \"self\" means the attention is applied "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "within"}, {"type": "text", "text": " a single sequence rather than between two different sequences (like a source and target in translation)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This is what gives Transformers their power: rather than processing tokens one-by-one (like RNNs), self-attention lets "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all tokens communicate with all other tokens simultaneously"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Self-Attention Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-attention is the core mechanism that enables modern AI models to understand context:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Capability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Long-range dependencies"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Any token can attend to any other, regardless of distance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Context-sensitive meaning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same word gets different representation depending on surrounding context"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parallelization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All tokens processed simultaneously (unlike sequential RNNs)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Resolves ambiguity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model learns which words relate to which others"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The classic example: in \"The animal didn't cross the street because "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "it"}, {"type": "text", "text": " was tired\" — self-attention allows the model to learn that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "\"it\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " refers to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "\"animal\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " by computing high attention between those two tokens."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Makes It \"Self\""}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The defining feature of self-attention is that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Queries, Keys, and Values all come from the same sequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regular attention (cross-attention):\n  Q from sequence A  ←  different sources\n  K and V from sequence B\n\nSelf-attention:\n  Q from sequence X  ←  SAME source\n  K from sequence X     for all three\n  V from sequence X"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The alignment scores are computed "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "between elements of the same sequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not between two different sequences. This is the fundamental distinction."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Self-Attention Works (Step-by-Step)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For every token in the sequence:"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Create Q, K, V from the input"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input: [\"The\", \"cat\", \"sat\"]\nEmbeddings: [e₁, e₂, e₃]\n\nFor each token, compute:\n  Q = embedding × W_Q\n  K = embedding × W_K\n  V = embedding × W_V\n\nQ = [Q_The, Q_cat, Q_sat]\nK = [K_The, K_cat, K_sat]\nV = [V_The, V_cat, V_sat]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 2: Compute attention scores for every token pair"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Score(cat, The) = Q_cat · K_The\nScore(cat, cat) = Q_cat · K_cat  ← token attending to itself\nScore(cat, sat) = Q_cat · K_sat\n\nRepeat for EVERY token in the sequence"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This produces an "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "n × n attention matrix"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (every token against every other)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 3: Scale and apply softmax"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaled score = score / √d_k\n\nSoftmax normalizes each row to sum to 1:\n  [0.1, 0.7, 0.2]  ← \"cat\" pays 70% attention to itself,\n                      20% to \"sat\", 10% to \"The\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 4: Weighted sum of Values"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "New representation of \"cat\" =\n  0.1 × V_The + 0.7 × V_cat + 0.2 × V_sat"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The result is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "context-aware embedding"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of \"cat\" that incorporates information from the whole sentence."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Complete Process Visually"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input sequence: [\"I\", \"bank\", \"by\", \"the\", \"river\"]\n\nSelf-Attention for \"bank\":\n  Q_bank compared against:\n    K_I      → score 0.05\n    K_bank   → score 0.20\n    K_by     → score 0.10\n    K_the    → score 0.05\n    K_river  → score 0.60 ← high score! \"river\" helps clarify \"bank\"\n  \n  Softmax weights: [0.05, 0.20, 0.10, 0.05, 0.60]\n  \n  New \"bank\" representation =\n    weighted sum of all V vectors\n    → Encodes \"bank\" as RIVERBANK, not financial bank\n\nContext changes meaning dynamically! 🎯"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Properties of Self-Attention"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bidirectional access"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each token sees all others simultaneously"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Position-agnostic"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention score depends on content, not position (positions added via positional encoding)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dynamic"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention weights change per input (not fixed like convolutions)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quadratic complexity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "O(n^{2} \\cdot d)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " — grows quadratically with sequence length"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-Attention vs. Traditional Attention"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Traditional Attention"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-Attention"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Source of Q"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder hidden state"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same input sequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Source of K, V"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder hidden states"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same input sequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Between"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Two different sequences"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Within one sequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder attends to encoder"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every token attends to every token"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variants of Self-Attention"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder Self-Attention (Bidirectional)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each token can attend to ALL other tokens — both before and after it:\n  \"bank\" attends to: \"I\", \"bank\", \"by\", \"the\", \"river\"\n  \nUsed in: BERT, encoders of BERT-like models"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder Masked Self-Attention (Causal/Unidirectional)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each token can only attend to PREVIOUS tokens (future masked):\n  \"river\" attends to: \"I\", \"bank\", \"by\", \"the\"\n  \"river\" CANNOT see future tokens\n  \nUsed in: GPT, autoregressive language models"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why masking?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " During generation, the model doesn't know future tokens. Masking prevents information leakage from future positions."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits of Self-Attention"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Long-range dependencies"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Direct path between any two tokens, regardless of distance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rich contextual representations"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each token's output incorporates context from the whole sequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parallelizable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All tokens computed simultaneously on GPUs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention weights visualizable to show what the model focuses on"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs & Limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quadratic cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "O(n^{2})"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " attention matrix — expensive for very long sequences"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No inherent order"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Needs positional encoding to understand sequence position"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory intensive"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large attention matrices for long sequences"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of self-attention as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "town meeting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " where every citizen can speak directly to every other citizen simultaneously:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Traditional RNN"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A game of telephone — tokens pass information one by one from left to right, losing quality at every step"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Self-attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Every token gets its own microphone and can hear everyone else at once — no information decay, no waiting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Or think of it as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "reading a paragraph and building a personal summary for each word"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every word asks: \"Which other words in this paragraph help explain my meaning?\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"Apple\" might weight \"fruit\" and \"eat\" highly → means the food"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"Apple\" might weight \"stock\" and \"market\" highly → means the company"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Self-attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": " computes attention between tokens of the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "same sequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", where Q, K, and V all come from the same input"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The word "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "\"self\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " means each token attends to all other tokens "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "within its own sequence"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Produces "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "context-aware representations"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": the same word gets a different embedding depending on surrounding context"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder self-attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (BERT) is bidirectional — tokens attend to all others"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder masked self-attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (GPT) is causal — tokens only attend to previous ones"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quadratic complexity"}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "O(n^{2})"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " limits application to very long sequences"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Requires "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "positional encoding"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to introduce order, since attention itself is position-agnostic"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-attention is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "heart of Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and powers models like GPT, BERT, and all modern large language models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-attention replaces the sequential bottleneck of RNNs with a fully parallel, globally-connected mechanism, enabling modern generative AI to understand complex long-range context efficiently."}]}]}}